Build Gate Proviso:
- Never render or expose spreadsheet letter identifiers in generated content or public-facing pages.
- Always use semantic entity names (for example, `Intervention Dominance`, `Coverage Timing`, `Evidence Type`).
- Treat any letter-identifier wording in generated outputs as a validation failure that must be fixed before build.

When creating or editing Functional Mechanism (FM) pages:

Follow:
- `system/functional-mechanism-schema.md`
- `system/mechanism-page-section-prose.md` — sections must not restate title, entity ID, BRS name/number, or Definition; each section follows only its schema role.

Synthesis contract (required):
- **FM pages are synthesis pages, not implementation pages.**
- **Ontology:** FMs are integrated biological states emerging from coordinated PMs — capacities, desired states or regulatory conditions; principal biological targets of the framework (`system/brain-diet-ontology-rules.md` §1.2).
- FM pages **synthesise** PMs; they do **not** repeat PM page content.
- **PMs own mechanisms and interventions. FMs own emergent integration.**
- **Interventions act on PMs.** Do **not** add Dietary Levers, Lifestyle Levers, or Scoreable Inputs to FM pages — those belong on constituent **PM pages**.
- **Definition (§1):** integrated regulatory state; do not paste full PM definitions.
- **Functional Role (§3):** short ↑ / ↓ **emergent FM outcomes** only — not PM delivery/incorporation language.
- **Mechanistic Basis (§4):** integrated narrative with linked PM/KC contributions — `### 4.1 Core Primary Mechanisms`, `### 4.2 Supporting Biological Pools (Key Constraints)`, `### 4.3 Integrated Functional Narrative`; open with why the FM matters; no PM citation dumps or `<details>` mechanism dumps.
- **§4.4 Evidence Highlights** *(optional)* — FM-level “why this integrated state matters”; not PM intervention/transport detail.
- **§5 Cross BRS Links** — roll up from constituent PM `§6 Cross BRS Links`; do not use legacy `BRS Links` heading on FM pages.
- **Deduplication:** if detail exists on a PM page, do not repeat it on the FM page — only describe how PMs combine into the FM state.

Structure:
- Canonical outline: **Definition → Intervention Breakdown → Functional Role → Mechanistic Basis (Integrated FM Narrative) → [optional §4.4] → Cross BRS Links → References** (`## 6.`).
- `mechanisms_covered` and `key_constraints` stay in **front matter** for tooling; PM/KC links render in §4.1/§4.2 only — no duplicate §5/§7 index lists.
- `timing_specific` (`Yes` | `No`) is **required in front matter**; do **not** add a standalone `## N. Timing Specific` body section.
- Where timing materially alters FM interpretation, discuss it in **Functional Role** or **Mechanistic Basis** — not Lifestyle/Scoreable sections on FM pages.
- The in-body title line must use markdown `##` (not `#` or `###`).
- Do not add Recipe Translation, Mechanism Summary Table, Underlying Mechanisms and Requirements, Dietary/Lifestyle/Scoreable sections, or other excluded blocks from `system/functional-mechanism-schema.md`.

Field interpretation:
- Front matter: `title`, `fm_id`, `parent_brs`, `summary`, `mechanisms_covered`, `key_constraints`, `intervention_breakdown`, `timing_specific`, `intervention_dominance`, `coverage_timing`, `references`
- `summary` must match §1 Definition intent per **FM Definition Rule**

Constraints:
- Must not introduce new PMs, FMs, or KCs without spreadsheet authority
- Must not include scoring formulas or raw scoring code on FM pages
- Use mechanistic, non-prescriptive framing in narrative
- Must not display PM/FM codes in recipe-facing examples beyond mechanism-page context

References:
- Use numeric citations [1], [2]
- All references must link to `/docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#citationKey`
- Verify citationKey exists in `static/bibtex/BRAIN-diet.bib`

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
